    <title>[PHP] Creating an index.php?xx=xx site</title>
    <link>https://forum.moparisthebest.com/t/php-creating-an-index-php-xx-xx-site/34653</link>
    <description>Maybe this could be useful to some of you, maybe not. Well, just take a look at it :) 

I hope you have a page with includes, for menu, header etc. For example:

&lt;html&gt;
&lt;title=&quot;My dynamic page&quot;&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
&lt;body&gt;

&lt;?php 
include(&quot;header.inc.php&quot;);
include(&quot;menu.inc.php&quot;);
// now comes the fun part

$show = $_GET[page];
// we&#39;re gonna include it
include(&quot;pages/&quot;.$show.&quot;.txt&quot;); // make a directory /pages/ with the page txt files in it.
?&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;


Now this will work. But what about the txt files? They&#39;re includes! An example of home.txt is:

&lt;!-- begin home --&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; This is so easy! &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;!-- end home --&gt;


That&#39;s all! Now you can easily make a menu with links like:
&lt;a href=&quot;index.php?page=home&quot;&gt;

That&#39;s all!
Hope you learned something from this ;)

~S!ms</description>
    
